body_html:
@uziela All of the errors are in bazel-out/host/bin/external/org_tensorflow/tensorflow/python/pywrap_tensorflow_internal.cc as far as I can tell, which isn't an XLA AOT specific file. However, I don't understand you're hitting this only when building with XLA AOT. Can you please run a bazel query (https://docs.bazel.build/versions/master/query-how-to.html) to find out how the target you're trying to build depends on pywrap_tensorflow_internal.cc?

There is also a way to disable building the python bindings: -Dtensorflow_BUILD_PYTHON_BINDINGS=(ON|OFF) (see https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/tree/master/tensorflow/contrib/cmake) -- perhaps you can use that as a workaround?
